messages.content:
This is a missed-optimization in SimplifyLibCalls.

The following program reveals the missed optimization.
The source program is
```llvm
define fp128 @fast_cabsl_neg_zero_imag(fp128 %real) {
  %call = tail call fast fp128 @cabsl(fp128 %real, fp128 0xL00000000000000008000000000000000)
  ret fp128 %call
}

declare fp128 @cabsl(fp128, fp128)

```

However, current LLVM cannot optimize the source program. The expected optimized program is
```llvm
define fp128 @fast_cabsl_neg_zero_imag(fp128 %real) {
  %cabs = tail call fast fp128 @llvm.fabs.f128(fp128 %real)
  ret fp128 %cabs
}

declare fp128 @cabsl(fp128, fp128)

; Function Attrs: nocallback nosync nounwind speculatable willreturn memory(none)
declare fp128 @llvm.fabs.f128(fp128) #0

attributes #0 = { nocallback nosync nounwind speculatable willreturn memory(none) }

```
Please modify the following code in llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyLibCalls.cpp:LibCallSimplifier::optimizeCAbs to implement the missed optimization:
